Revenue collections in wildlife management areas (WMAs) increased in the past three years. According to Makao WMA secretary Robert Simon, Sh294 million was collected in 2016/17, up from Sh34.1 million in 2013/14. The amount is expected to reach Sh428.8 million in 2017/18. Maswa Game Reserve tourism official Elibariki Wakomalwa said the revenue collection rose from Sh110 million in 2014/15 to Sh312 million in 2016/17.